This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with computational humor and language processing. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of models for humor detection. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves the analysis of tweets and hashtags. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the collection and analysis of a large dataset.
